TI  - Encroachment of complementary suppliers in the technology product market
AU  - Wu, Xiangxiang
AU  - Zha, Yong
T2  - EXPERT SYSTEMS WITH APPLICATIONS
AB  - This study aims to delve deeply into the supply chain relationship between hardware manufacturers and software platform owners in the technology product market, particularly how both parties attempt to encroach upon each other's core business areas while maintaining cooperation. To be specific, we examine the sequential encroachment decisions between a manufacturer and a platform owner, where both parties may choose between cooperative encroachment and self-design encroachment to enter the end-product market. In constructing a game-theoretic model, we consider a scenario where the manufacturer initially makes the encroachment decision, followed by the platform owner's encroachment decision, and finally, both parties set their products' component and retail prices under two cases of differing user preferences. In the case where users have a higher preference for the manufacturer's product than that of the platform, our analysis interestingly shows that, given the manufacturer's cooperative encroachment, the platform always tends to choose self-design encroachment. In the case of the platform having a higher user preference, the manufacturer has a similar inclination when anticipating the platform chooses cooperative encroachment. In the platform's optimal choice, both parties may be more beneficial under self-design or cooperative encroachment when the platform has a higher user preference, but can be more favorable only under self-design encroachment when the manufacturer has a higher user preference. Furthermore, we find that symmetric cooperative encroachment is never an equilibrium configuration, while the other encroachment configurations may appear in equilibrium, depending on the size of the software design cost and the user preference differences. Our study provides important insights regarding encroachment for complementary participants in the technology product market.
